{"questionId":"5442","questionHtml":"<p>Which equation shows oxygen undergoing reduction?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2F<sub>2</sub> + O<sub>2</sub> → 2F<sub>2</sub>O</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Na<sub>2</sub>O + H<sub>2</sub>O → 2NaOH</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub> + 2HI → 2H<sub>2</sub>O + I<sub>2</sub></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2CrO<sub>4</sub><sup>2−</sup> + 2H<sup>+</sup> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> Cr<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub><sup>2−</sup> + H<sub>2</sub>O</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5442","referenceCode":"18M.1.sl.TZ1.21","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Which equation shows oxygen undergoing reduction? A. 2F2 + O2 → 2F2O B. Na2O + H2O → 2NaOH C. H2O2 + 2HI → 2H2O + I2 D. 2CrO42− + 2H+ ⇌ Cr2O72− + H2O","paper":"1","level":"sl","questionNumber":"21","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 9: Redox processes","9.1 Oxidation and reduction","Core","Topic 9: Redox processes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}